Place beef steak in a plastic bag. Combine garlic, sherry, soy sauce, oil and ginger; reserve 1/4 cup. Pour remaining marinade over the steak. Close bag securely and marinate in refrigerator 4 to 8 hours, turning at least once. Meanwhile prepare Relish: Combine vegetable oil, sesame oil, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and hot pepper sauce. Add green onions, mushrooms and bell peppers. Let stand for 30 minutes. Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade. Place steak on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 4 inches from heat. Broil for 15-18 minutes, turning once and basting with reserved marinade. Let stand for 5 minutes. Meanwhile split hoagie rolls and toast under the broiler. Carve steak diagonally across the grain in two slices. Place beef in hoagie rolls. Top with relish and serve.